    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.HSA-APR.C.4</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Prove polynomial identities and use them to describe numerical relationships. &lt;i&gt;For example, the polynomial identity (x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = (x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; &amp;ndash; y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + (2xy)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; can be used to generate Pythagorean triples.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</Statement>
    </Statements>
